  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Poster</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1932 after</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The poster advertises the sound feature ‘Visul lui Tănase’ (Tănase’s dream), produced by ‘Tobis-Klang-Berlin’. The film title is displayed in the lower part of the poster. The drawing features a man’s face and a woman with fair hair walking along his long nose. Another woman is sitting on his nose holding a saxophone. Another man with a long nose is running away, carrying suitcases.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The feature was directed by Bernd Aldor with Constantin Tănase in the leading role. The film was released in 1932. ‘Tobis-Klang’ was a German film production company.</ab>
